    <fr:title text="Small-step operation semantics">Small-step operation semantics</fr:title>
    <fr:authors />
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>A small-step semantics for a language ${T} of syntactic terms comprises two components:

<fr:ul><fr:li>a set of <fr:em>execution states</fr:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>a <fr:em>transition relation</fr:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s \rightarrow  s']]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> that relates each state
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex> to each state <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s']]></fr:tex> that may be reached by performaing a single execution step</fr:li></fr:ul></fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
