            <fr:title text="Operational semantics">Operational semantics</fr:title>
            <fr:authors />
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>The <fr:em>operational semantics</fr:em> defines the meaning of terms in a langauge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[T]]></fr:tex> using an
<fr:em>execution relation</fr:em> that specifies how terms can be executed in an appropriate machine
model.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>There are two forms of operations semantics:

<fr:ul><fr:li><fr:strong>small-step operational semantics</fr:strong> which describes the individual execution steps</fr:li>
<fr:li><fr:strong>big-step operational semantics</fr:strong> which describes the overall results of execution</fr:li></fr:ul></fr:p>
            <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
              <fr:frontmatter>
